ZH: 我的手套掉在地上了。
EN: My gloves fell on the ground.

ZH: 她穿着一双漂亮的手套。
EN: She is wearing a pair of beautiful gloves.

ZH: 这双手套太小了，戴不下。
EN: These gloves are too small to fit.

ZH: 我们在冬天里总是戴手套。
EN: We always wear gloves in winter.

ZH: 每次出门我都必须带一双手套。
EN: I have to bring a pair of gloves every time I go out.

ZH: 他不小心把手套遗忘在车上了。
EN: He accidentally left his gloves in the car.

ZH: 这双手套很暖和。
EN: These gloves are very warm.

ZH: 我在商店里买了一双手套。
EN: I bought a pair of gloves at the store.

ZH: 好朋友送给我一双手套。
EN: My good friend gave me a pair of gloves.

ZH: 手套是在昨晚被遗失的。
EN: The gloves were lost last night.

ZH: 这个手套是我的最爱。
EN: This glove is my favorite.

ZH: 姐姐不喜欢戴手套。
EN: My sister does not like wearing gloves.

ZH: 警察戴着手套开始调查。
EN: The police officer put on gloves to start the investigation.

ZH: 这双手套和我的大衣搭配得很好。
EN: These gloves match my coat perfectly.

ZH: 我的手套已经破了，需要换新的。
EN: My gloves are already torn and need to be replaced.

ZH: 他的手套很贵，是名牌。
EN: His gloves are expensive, they are branded.

ZH: 奶奶每天都在针织新手套。
EN: Grandma knits new gloves every day.

ZH: 我的儿子经常弄丢手套。
EN: My son often loses his gloves.

ZH: 给我一双手套，我手冷。
EN: Give me a pair of gloves, my hands are cold.

ZH: 我的手套已经变形了，需要找人修理。
EN: My gloves are deformed and need to be repaired.
